<topic id="author-attributes-view">
  <title>Attributes View in Author Mode</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Author editing mode<indexterm>Attributes view</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML documents<indexterm>Author Mode editing<indexterm>Attributes
            view</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Attributes view in Author Mode</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/attribute-view-intro"/>
    <p>You can use this view to edit or add attribute values. The attributes of an element are
      editable if any one of the following is true:<ul id="ul_nfn_z5r_n2">
        <li>The CSS stylesheet associated with the document does not specify a
            <uicontrol>false</uicontrol> value for the <xref
            href="../topics/dg-editable-css-extension.dita#dg-editable-css-extension" format="dita"
            >-oxy-editable</xref> property associated with the element.</li>
        <li>The element is entirely included in a deleted <xref
            href="../topics/author-change-tracking.dita#author-change-tracking/change-tracking"
            format="dita"><term>Track Changes</term></xref> marker.</li>
        <li>The element is part of a content fragment that is referenced in
            <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode from another document.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/attribute-view-rendering"/>
    <note>If the cursor is located inside read-only content, the attribute names and values are
      faded and you cannot add, edit, or remove values. </note>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/attribute-view-sorting"/>
    <p>
      <fig product="editor author">
        <title>Attributes View</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_author_attributes_panel.png"/>
